        "theme":  "Enterprise",
        "summary":  "ING\u0027s Global CIO of Wholesale Banking explains that AI transformation success depends more on foundational infrastructure than on the technology itself. The podcast highlights three production-scale wins: a personalized messaging engine at millions-of-customers scale, KYC automation cutting manual work by 80%, and agentic AI in lending operations. Banks with modernized platforms can move AI pilots to production in weeks; those without remain perpetually stalled.",
        "execSummary":  "ING\u0027s experience offers a clear-eyed diagnosis for enterprises whose AI pilots never graduate to production: the constraint is almost never the model, it is the underlying data and platform foundation. An 80% reduction in KYC manual work and weeks-to-production timelines are only achievable because ING rebuilt its infrastructure before scaling AIΓÇöa sequence most organizations are attempting in reverse. For senior leaders, the implication is that AI budget approval without a parallel infrastructure modernization commitment will continue to produce demo-grade results at enterprise cost. This is a direct counter-argument to the common pressure to show AI ROI before investing in the platform that makes ROI possible.",
