        "url":  "https://www.ciodive.com/news/keep-ai-costs-in-check-agentic-drives-usage/825476/",
        "date":  "2026-07-17",
        "theme":  "Agents",
        "summary":  "Two-thirds of IT professionals lack visibility into their organization\u0027s AI software spending, even as agentic AI dramatically accelerates consumption. OpenAI outlined a five-strategy cost management framework covering usage visibility, outcome-based tracking, governance controls, AI portfolio management, and scaling only proven workflows. Enterprises like Prudential Financial and Shutterstock are actively restructuring AI spending governance to manage the cost acceleration that agentic workloads introduce.",
        "execSummary":  "Agentic AI is creating a cost governance emergency: most enterprises cannot see what they are spending on AI, and agentic workloads are multiplying token consumption far faster than seat-based budgets anticipated. OpenAI\u0027s five-point framework is a starting point, but the deeper issue is that traditional software procurement and chargeback models have no mechanism for the variable, action-multiplying consumption pattern agentic systems produce. For CIOs and CFOs, the immediate priority is instrumenting AI usage at the workflow level before committing to agentic scaleΓÇöthe cost surprise compounds quickly once agents are running autonomously across systems. Enterprises that skip this step are likely to face budget overruns that stall broader AI programs mid-deployment.",
