        "summary":  "An SAP and Oxford Economics study of 2,600 executives finds AI satisfaction has reached 69%, but ROI is materializing in unexpected placesΓÇöprimarily in business insights and customer engagement rather than cost savings or productivity. Companies are struggling to measure AI\u0027s full value because their metrics frameworks were built around efficiency, not the insight-generation and engagement patterns where AI is actually delivering.",
