        "summary":  "Rather than chasing the latest model releases, enterprises should anchor decisions to specific job requirements and establish performance benchmarks before selecting a model. The article argues that data quality, workflows, and integrations matter far more than which model is trending, and recommends starting with lower-cost options that clear defined performance thresholds. Model-agnostic architecture insulates companies from the rapid pace of model churn.",
